    "Post-Use Perceptions + InterviewPerform a different personalization task with each chatbot: and have access to the conversation history, which means that even the unsteered model can adjust its outputs to reflect the prompts of the user.",
    "We hypothesize that the models that were significantly affected by prompting in E2, e.g.",
    "gemma-2-9b-it, would be more adaptive through prompting alone, which is reflected in a lack of significance between Learned and Baseline (see Figure F.1).",
    "Nevertheless, the learned steering approach demonstrates potential to dynamically adjust steering based on the sentiment of user feedback.",
    "This allows for light-weight, inference time personalization and is especially applicable to cold-start scenarios."
